{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QkNmK9kmagc1AdgujEaEef","type":"tool_result","content":"   280→referral_kol_rates (\n   281→  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   282→  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n   283→  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n   284→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   285→  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   286→)\n   287→```\n   288→\n   289→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   290→- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n   291→- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 — referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   292→- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 — code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   293→- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n   294→- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 — CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n   295→- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 — CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n   296→\n   297→### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n   298→\n   299→All frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n   300→\n   301→#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n   302→\n   303→A lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   304→\n   305→**Flow:**\n   306→1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n   307→2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   308→3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   309→4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   310→5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n   311→\n   312→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   313→- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   314→- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n   315→- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n   316→- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   317→- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n   318→- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n   319→\n   320→#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n   321→\n   322→New nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   323→\n   324→```tsx\n   325→<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   326→  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   327→  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   328→    {/* share/link icon */}\n   329→  </div>\n   330→  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   331→</NavLink>\n   332→```\n   333→\n   334→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   335→- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n   336→- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   337→- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   338→- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   339→\n   340→#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   341→\n   342→Main referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   343→\n   344→**Layout — top to bottom:**\n   345→\n   346→1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   347→   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   348→   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   349→   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   350→   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351→\n   352→2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353→   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354→   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355→   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356→   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357→\n   358→3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359→   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360→   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361→   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   362→   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363→\n   364→4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365→   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366→   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367→   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368→   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369→\n   370→**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371→\n   372→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373→- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374→- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375→- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376→- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377→- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378→- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379→- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380→- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381→- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382→- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383→\n   384→#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n   385→\n   386→In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387→\n   388→**Layout:**\n   389→- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390→- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391→- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392→- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393→\n   394→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395→- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396→- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397→- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398→- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399→- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400→\n   401→#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402→\n   403→Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404→\n   405→```typescript\n   406→const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407→\n   408→export async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409→export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410→export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411→export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412→export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413→export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414→export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418→- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419→- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420→- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421→- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422→\n   423→#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n   424→\n   425→A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426→\n   427→```typescript\n   428→// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429→export function useReferralApply() {\n   430→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431→  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432→\n   433→  useEffect(() => {\n   434→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435→    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436→    if (!stored) return;\n   437→    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439→      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440→      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442→}\n   443→```\n   444→\n   445→Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446→\n   447→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448→- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449→- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450→- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451→- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452→- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453→- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454→\n   455→### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456→\n   457→The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458→\n   459→**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460→1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461→2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n   462→3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463→4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464→\n   465→**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466→1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467→2. If found → use KOL rate\n   468→3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469→\n   470→**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471→\n   472→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473→- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474→- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475→- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476→- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477→- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478→- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479→- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"b89c16ce-daf2-49fd-85d6-0dbcd56f10fd","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:33:42.805Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"referral_kol_rates (\n  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 — referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 — code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 — CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 — CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n\n### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n\nAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n\n#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout — top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found → use KOL rate\n3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->","numLines":200,"startLine":280,"totalLines":715}}}
