{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BuHYmPFUtWuvUpy7cnwRVZ","type":"tool_result","content":"   550→- Fixed pre-existing integration test bug: added PlatformConfig mock account setup (settlement reads fee_bps from PlatformConfig PDA, not CoinflipConfig PDA). All 4 original tests were silently broken by this.\n   551→- Added `buildPlatformConfigData()` helper to construct mock PlatformConfig account data (8-byte disc + 32-byte authority + 32-byte treasury + 2-byte fee_bps)\n   552→- Added `resetPlatformConfigCache()` export to `platform-config.ts` for test isolation\n   553→- Added Unix socket fallback via `makeSql()` helper (same pattern as referral-routes.test.ts)\n   554→- Added referral migration execution in `beforeAll` (idempotent)\n   555→- Added referral tables to TRUNCATE in `beforeEach` for isolation\n   556→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). All 6 integration tests pass (4 original + 2 new).\n   557→\n   558→## Iteration 29 — 2026-03-25T14:07:02Z — OK\n   559→- **Log**: iteration-029.log\n   560→\n   561→## Iteration 30 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   562→\n   563→**Item**: [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**`\n   564→**Status**: Done\n   565→**Changes**:\n   566→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/30-referral.spec.ts` with Playwright test covering the primary referral user flow:\n   567→  - Player A navigates to `/referrals`, sets custom referral code \"e2e-ref-test\", verifies URL display mode\n   568→  - Verifies all page sections render (stats card, claim card, earnings table with empty state)\n   569→  - Player B visits `/r/e2e-ref-test` → ReferralCapture stores code in localStorage → redirects to `/` → `useReferralApply` hook auto-applies on auth\n   570→  - Waits for `POST /referral/apply` response (200) to confirm apply succeeded\n   571→  - Player B navigates to `/profile` → Settings tab → verifies \"Referred by:\" linked status\n   572→  - Player A refreshes `