{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AfxDiWSB8xqyHheyGXqzjR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Findings Report: ReferralPage Component Analysis\n\n### 1. CSS Classes Rendered by State\n\n**Disconnected State** (wallet not connected OR not authenticated):\n- Renders: `.referral-page__connect` (lines 14-25 in ReferralPage.tsx)\n- Contains: h2 title, description paragraphs, \"Connect your wallet\" prompt\n- This is shown when `!connected || !isAuthenticated` (line 12)\n\n**Connected & Authenticated State** (wallet connected AND authenticated):\n- Renders: `.referral-page__content` (lines 37-42 in ReferralPage.tsx)\n- Contains: All referral cards (ReferralLinkCard, ReferralStatsCard, ReferralClaimCard, ReferralEarningsTable)\n- Also renders: `.referral-page__header`, `.referral-page__title`, `.referral-page__subtitle` (lines 30-34)\n- This is shown when both `connected && isAuthenticated` are true\n\n### 2. Authentication Requirements\n\n**ReferralPage requires BOTH wallet connection AND authentication:**\n\nThe component checks two conditions on line 12:\n```javascript\nif (!connected || !isAuthenticated) {\n  return <div className=\"referral-page__connect\">...\n}\n```\n\nThis means:\n- `.referral-page__connect` is shown when wallet is disconnected **OR** when authentication has not yet completed\n- `.referral-page__content` is only shown when **both** `connected=true` AND `isAuthenticated=true`\n\n**Authentication flow** (from SessionContext.tsx):\n- Wallet connection triggers automatic authentication attempt (lines 174-220)\n- The `authenticate()` function performs challenge-response signing:\n  1. Request challenge from backend\n  2. Sign the message with wallet's private key (line 145)\n  3. Verify signature with backend to get JWT tokens (line 149)\n  4. Store access token and refresh token (line 152-158)\n  5. Set `isAuthenticated = true` (line 160)\n- Even if wallet is connected but JWT authentication fails, `isAuthenticated` remains `false`\n\n### 3. How \"Connected\" Works in Visual Tests\n\nLooking at `states.spec.ts` (lines 289-342 for referrals test), \"connected\" in visual test context means:\n\n1. **Wallet connection** (not just connection, but with mock wallet that generates from seeded PRNG):\n   - User clears localStorage to ensure fresh state (line 305-307)\n   - User navigates to page (line 308)\n   - User clicks `.rng-wallet-button--disconnected` button (line 311)\n   - Test waits for `.rng-wallet-button--connected` selector (line 314-316)\n\n2. **Authentication** (automatically triggered after wallet connection):\n   - Once wallet is connected, SessionContext automatically calls `authenticate()` (SessionContext.tsx line 217)\n   - In the visual test environment, the authentication appears to succeed automatically when backend is available\n   - The test then waits for `.referral-page__content` to appear (line 319-321), proving authentication completed\n\n3. **What's being mocked**:\n   - The `stablePage` fixture (fixtures.ts lines 25-121):\n     - Seeds `Math.random()` and `crypto.getRandomValues()` for deterministic keypair generation\n     - Freezes `Date.now()` to a fixed timestamp\n     - Disables animations/transitions\n     - Injects CSS freeze\n     - Waits for network idle and fonts to load\n   - Does NOT mock the actual authentication API calls — it relies on backend being reachable\n   - Wallet adapter appears to use localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`) to persist connection state\n\n### 4. Key Differences from Other Pages\n\nThe referrals page test differs from other pages (e.g., home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs) because:\n- **Coinflip/LoR/HomeBase pages**: Only check wallet `connected` state; show game UI when connected, show connect prompt when disconnected\n- **ReferralsPage**: Requires **both** `connected` AND `isAuthenticated` state\n  - This means the visual test must wait for TWO conditions: wallet button shows connected AND referral content appears\n  - Wallet connection alone is insufficient — backend authentication must complete\n\n### 5. File Paths\n\n- **ReferralPage component**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ReferralPage.tsx`\n- **SessionContext (auth logic)**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n- **Visual test fixture**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- **Referrals state tests**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts` (lines 289-342)\n- **ReferralLinkCard** (uses accessToken): `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ReferralLinkCard.tsx`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a32d38bc3181b218b (use SendMessage with to: 'a32d38bc3181b218b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56713\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 32373</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"cf29972b-9d36-44c7-a6f8-5656f695fda1","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:47:56.102Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the ReferralPage component in the platform app (sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/). I need to know:\n1. What CSS classes it renders in connected vs disconnected state\n2. Specifically look for `.referral-page__content` and `.referral-page__connect` class names\n3. Whether it requires authentication (not just wallet connection) to show the content\n\nSearch in sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ and any files that import or reference ReferralPage.\n\nAlso check how other connected-state visual tests work — what does \"connected\" mean in the visual test context? Do they call a mock auth endpoint or just mock the wallet connection?\n\nLook at the e2e/fixtures.ts to understand the stablePage fixture and how wallet connection works in visual tests.","agentId":"a32d38bc3181b218b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Findings Report: ReferralPage Component Analysis\n\n### 1. CSS Classes Rendered by State\n\n**Disconnected State** (wallet not connected OR not authenticated):\n- Renders: `.referral-page__connect` (lines 14-25 in ReferralPage.tsx)\n- Contains: h2 title, description paragraphs, \"Connect your wallet\" prompt\n- This is shown when `!connected || !isAuthenticated` (line 12)\n\n**Connected & Authenticated State** (wallet connected AND authenticated):\n- Renders: `.referral-page__content` (lines 37-42 in ReferralPage.tsx)\n- Contains: All referral cards (ReferralLinkCard, ReferralStatsCard, ReferralClaimCard, ReferralEarningsTable)\n- Also renders: `.referral-page__header`, `.referral-page__title`, `.referral-page__subtitle` (lines 30-34)\n- This is shown when both `connected && isAuthenticated` are true\n\n### 2. Authentication Requirements\n\n**ReferralPage requires BOTH wallet connection AND authentication:**\n\nThe component checks two conditions on line 12:\n```javascript\nif (!connected || !isAuthenticated) {\n  return <div className=\"referral-page__connect\">...\n}\n```\n\nThis means:\n- `.referral-page__connect` is shown when wallet is disconnected **OR** when authentication has not yet completed\n- `.referral-page__content` is only shown when **both** `connected=true` AND `isAuthenticated=true`\n\n**Authentication flow** (from SessionContext.tsx):\n- Wallet connection triggers automatic authentication attempt (lines 174-220)\n- The `authenticate()` function performs challenge-response signing:\n  1. Request challenge from backend\n  2. Sign the message with wallet's private key (line 145)\n  3. Verify signature with backend to get JWT tokens (line 149)\n  4. Store access token and refresh token (line 152-158)\n  5. Set `isAuthenticated = true` (line 160)\n- Even if wallet is connected but JWT authentication fails, `isAuthenticated` remains `false`\n\n### 3. How \"Connected\" Works in Visual Tests\n\nLooking at `states.spec.ts` (lines 289-342 for referrals test), \"connected\" in visual test context means:\n\n1. **Wallet connection** (not just connection, but with mock wallet that generates from seeded PRNG):\n   - User clears localStorage to ensure fresh state (line 305-307)\n   - User navigates to page (line 308)\n   - User clicks `.rng-wallet-button--disconnected` button (line 311)\n   - Test waits for `.rng-wallet-button--connected` selector (line 314-316)\n\n2. **Authentication** (automatically triggered after wallet connection):\n   - Once wallet is connected, SessionContext automatically calls `authenticate()` (SessionContext.tsx line 217)\n   - In the visual test environment, the authentication appears to succeed automatically when backend is available\n   - The test then waits for `.referral-page__content` to appear (line 319-321), proving authentication completed\n\n3. **What's being mocked**:\n   - The `stablePage` fixture (fixtures.ts lines 25-121):\n     - Seeds `Math.random()` and `crypto.getRandomValues()` for deterministic keypair generation\n     - Freezes `Date.now()` to a fixed timestamp\n     - Disables animations/transitions\n     - Injects CSS freeze\n     - Waits for network idle and fonts to load\n   - Does NOT mock the actual authentication API calls — it relies on backend being reachable\n   - Wallet adapter appears to use localStorage (`rng-utopia-mock-wallet`) to persist connection state\n\n### 4. Key Differences from Other Pages\n\nThe referrals page test differs from other pages (e.g., home, coinflip, lord-of-rngs) because:\n- **Coinflip/LoR/HomeBase pages**: Only check wallet `connected` state; show game UI when connected, show connect prompt when disconnected\n- **ReferralsPage**: Requires **both** `connected` AND `isAuthenticated` state\n  - This means the visual test must wait for TWO conditions: wallet button shows connected AND referral content appears\n  - Wallet connection alone is insufficient — backend authentication must complete\n\n### 5. File Paths\n\n- **ReferralPage component**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ReferralPage.tsx`\n- **SessionContext (auth logic)**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx`\n- **Visual test fixture**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- **Referrals state tests**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts` (lines 289-342)\n- **ReferralLinkCard** (uses accessToken): `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/referral/ReferralLinkCard.tsx`"}],"totalDurationMs":32373,"totalTokens":56713,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1107,"cache_read_input_tokens":54313,"output_tokens":1286,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1107},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
