{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TSgaEy1ERNeupyktggHber","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ProfilePage doesn't check `isAuthenticated` at all - it seems to render regardless. Only the ReferralPage has this gate. The issue is that in mock/visual mode with no backend, authentication fails silently, so the ReferralPage stays in the \"connect\" state even after wallet is connected.\n\nI have two options:\n1. Fix the visual test to not require authentication (use a different approach)\n2. Fix the ReferralPage to show content when connected but not authenticated\n3. Mock the authentication in the test\n\nLooking at the visual test approach, other \"connected\" tests don't need auth. The simplest fix would be to modify the ReferralPage to show the main content when `connected` is true (like all other pages), and only use `isAuthenticated` for API calls within the sub-components. \n\nThe sub-components can handle the unauthenticated state gracefully, so the cleanest approach is to update the ReferralPage to only check `connected` instead of `isAuthenticated` — the auth-gated API calls are already handled by the sub-components anyway.\n\nBut looking at the spec again, FR-9c requires both wallet connection and authentication, yet the visual test only connects a mock wallet without authenticating. Since authentication can't succeed in mock mode without a backend, the test was fundamentally broken from the start — that's why baseline generation was deferred. I need to either modify the test to account for this limitation or find another approach.\n\nThe simplest fix would be to skip waiting for authenticated content and just screenshot whatever state appears after wallet connection, but that would produce a misleading test since it'd look identical to the disconnected state. Changing the business logic to only check `connected` instead of `isAuthenticated` would be wrong. The right solution is to mock the auth responses using Playwright's route interception, so I need to figure out how the dev server is configured and what the auth endpoint URL is.\n\nLooking at the setup, the frontend dev server runs Vite and makes auth calls to `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL`, which in mock mode probably points to `http://127.0.0.1:3100` where no backend is actually running. I can use Playwright's `page.route()` to intercept those auth API calls and return mock responses instead.\n\nBut wait — I'm supposed to be updating visual baselines, not fixing the test itself. The checklist is clear about that. The test should have been working already from the previous iteration, so something went wrong with how the referrals page test was set up.\n\nLooking at the actual failure, after wallet connection the page still shows the \"Connect your wallet\" prompt because `isAuthenticated` is false. The fastest fix is to mock the auth API calls in the test using `page.route()` so the authentication succeeds and the page renders properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":143,"cache_read_input_tokens":79031,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":143},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"5734933e-163a-4e9c-90f6-a502c0b194f3"}
