{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017mgr3Ti36qcZSp66ngNx1W","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Thin fetch wrappers for the /auth/* backend endpoints.\n     3→ */\n     4→\n     5→const BACKEND_URL = (\n     6→  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n     7→    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n     8→).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n     9→\n    10→export interface ChallengeResponse {\n    11→  nonce: string;\n    12→  message: string;\n    13→  expiresAt: string;\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→export interface VerifyResponse {\n    17→  accessToken: string;\n    18→  accessExpiresAt: string;\n    19→  refreshToken: string;\n    20→  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n    21→}\n    22→\n    23→export interface RefreshResponse {\n    24→  accessToken: string;\n    25→  accessExpiresAt: string;\n    26→  refreshToken: string;\n    27→  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→async function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n    31→  const json = await res.json();\n    32→  if (!res.ok) {\n    33→    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    34→    throw new Error(msg);\n    35→  }\n    36→  return json as T;\n    37→}\n    38→\n    39→export async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n    40→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    41→    method: \"POST\",\n    42→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    43→    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n    44→  });\n    45→  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n    46→}\n    47→\n    48→export async function verifyChallenge(\n    49→  nonce: string,\n    50→  wallet: string,\n    51→  signature: string,\n    52→): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n    53→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    54→    method: \"POST\",\n    55→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    56→    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n    57→  });\n    58→  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n    59→}\n    60→\n    61→export async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n    62→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    63→    method: \"POST\",\n    64→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    65→    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n    66→  });\n    67→  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→export async function logout(refreshToken: string): Promise<void> {\n    71→  await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/logout`, {\n    72→    method: \"POST\",\n    73→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    74→    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n    75→  });\n    76→}\n    77→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"fb1697dd-a33d-4e97-9281-05d5416bcccb","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:49:56.724Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts","content":"/**\n * Thin fetch wrappers for the /auth/* backend endpoints.\n */\n\nconst BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n\nexport interface ChallengeResponse {\n  nonce: string;\n  message: string;\n  expiresAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface VerifyResponse {\n  accessToken: string;\n  accessExpiresAt: string;\n  refreshToken: string;\n  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface RefreshResponse {\n  accessToken: string;\n  accessExpiresAt: string;\n  refreshToken: string;\n  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n}\n\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n\nexport async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function verifyChallenge(\n  nonce: string,\n  wallet: string,\n  signature: string,\n): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function logout(refreshToken: string): Promise<void> {\n  await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/logout`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n}\n","numLines":77,"startLine":1,"totalLines":77}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LicVj9AJDQzg1ZmiiWbSD4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to check how the visual test fixture works, specifically for the Profile page \"wallet connected\" test which also needs auth to access `accessToken` in ProfileSettings. Let me check if the Profile page rendering is somehow different — maybe it renders without auth but just has some API calls that fail silently.\n\nActually, looking at the Profile page connected test (states.spec.ts:51-88), it just:\n1. Connects the wallet\n2. Waits for `.rng-wallet-button--connected`\n3. Takes a screenshot\n\nIt doesn't wait for any auth-gated content. \n\nSo the ProfilePage renders without checking `isAuthenticated` at the top level — only ProfileSettings uses `useSession()` and handles a missing `accessToken` gracefully. The ReferralPage is the problem here since it has a hard gate requiring both `connected` and `isAuthenticated`. I could either mock the auth API in the visual test or remove the `isAuthenticated` check from the ReferralPage gate so it renders in the \"connected but not authenticated\" state and lets sub-components handle the missing auth themselves. The second approach feels cleaner architecturally.\n\nBut the spec explicitly requires both wallet connection and authentication, so mocking the auth endpoints is the right move — it doesn't change the business logic. I need to intercept the challenge and verify endpoints in the Playwright test. Let me check if there's already a route handler pattern in the fixtures or if other visual tests are already mocking auth. The tricky part is that after auth succeeds, the page would call the referral API endpoints, which would also need to be mocked or they'd fail and the sub-components would have to handle those errors gracefully.\n\nSetting up route interception for the auth endpoints plus the referral endpoints... zeros, empty earnings table, a