{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W1LZA1P6nenWw29tcRbPWz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { test as base, expect, type Page, type ConsoleMessage } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     2→\n     3→const FREEZE_CSS = `\n     4→  *, *::before, *::after {\n     5→    animation-duration: 0s !important;\n     6→    animation-delay: 0s !important;\n     7→    transition-duration: 0s !important;\n     8→    transition-delay: 0s !important;\n     9→    scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n    10→  }\n    11→  /* Pause SVG SMIL animations */\n    12→  svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n    13→`;\n    14→\n    15→/**\n    16→ * Shared visual-regression fixture.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * Extends the default Playwright `test` with a `stablePage` fixture that:\n    19→ *  (a) Seeds Math.random() and Date.now() for determinism\n    20→ *  (b) Injects CSS to disable all CSS + SVG animations/transitions\n    21→ *  (c) Pauses SVG SMIL animations via JS\n    22→ *  (d) Waits for document.fonts.ready and network idle\n    23→ *  (e) Collects console errors and fails the test if any are found\n    24→ */\n    25→export const test = base.extend<{ stablePage: Page }>({\n    26→  stablePage: async ({ page }, use) => {\n    27→    // (e) Collect console errors throughout the test (filtering expected noise)\n    28→    const NOISE_PATTERNS = [\n    29→      \"401\",                 // JWT auth attempts in mock mode (no backend)\n    30→      \"403\",                 // Auth rejection in mock mode\n    31→      \"429\",                 // Rate limit (multiple visual tests hit same endpoints)\n    32→      \"favicon\",             // Missing favicon\n    33→      \"ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED\", // Backend not running in visual test mode\n    34→      \"Failed to fetch\",     // Network requests to non-existent backend\n    35→      \"Failed to load resource\", // Generic resource loading failures (auth, rate limit)\n    36→      \"NetworkError\",        // Same\n    37→    ];\n    38→    const consoleErrors: string[] = [];\n    39→    page.on(\"console\", (msg: ConsoleMessage) => {\n    40→      if (msg.type() === \"error\") {\n    41→        const text = msg.text();\n    42→        if (!NOISE_PATTERNS.some((p) => text.includes(p))) {\n    43→          consoleErrors.push(text);\n    44→        }\n    45→      }\n    46→    });\n    47→\n    48→    // (a) Deterministic Math.random, crypto.getRandomValues, and frozen Date.now\n    49→    await page.addInitScript(() => {\n    50→      // Mulberry32 seeded PRNG — deterministic sequence from seed 42\n    51→      let seed = 42;\n    52→      function mulberry32(): number {\n    53→        seed |= 0;\n    54→        seed = (seed + 0x6d2b79f5) | 0;\n    55→        let t = Math.imul(seed ^ (seed >>> 15), 1 | seed);\n    56→        t = (t + Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 7), 61 | t)) ^ t;\n    57→        return ((t ^ (t >>> 14)) >>> 0) / 4294967296;\n    58→      }\n    59→\n    60→      Math.random = mulberry32;\n    61→\n    62→      // Also seed crypto.getRandomValues so Keypair.generate() is deterministic\n    63→      crypto.getRandomValues = <T extends ArrayBufferView | null>(array: T): T => {\n    64→        if (array === null) return array;\n    65→        const view = new Uint8Array(\n    66→          (array as ArrayBufferView).buffer,\n    67→          (array as ArrayBufferView).byteOffset,\n    68→          (array as ArrayBufferView).byteLength,\n    69→        );\n    70→        for (let i = 0; i < view.length; i++) {\n    71→          view[i] = Math.floor(mulberry32() * 256);\n    72→        }\n    73→        return array;\n    74→      };\n    75→\n    76→      // Freeze Date.now to a fixed timestamp (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n    77→      const frozen = 1767225600000;\n    78→      Date.now = () => frozen;\n    79→    });\n    80→\n    81→    // Store the original goto so we can wrap it\n    82→    const originalGoto = page.goto.bind(page);\n    83→\n    84→    // Override goto to always wait for fonts + network idle after navigation\n    85→    page.goto = async (url: string, options?: Parameters<typeof page.goto>[1]) => {\n    86→      const response = await originalGoto(url, {\n    87→        waitUntil: \"networkidle\",\n    88→        ...options,\n    89→      });\n    90→\n    91→      // (b) Inject animation-disabling CSS (navigation clears addStyleTag)\n    92→      await page.addStyleTag({ content: FREEZE_CSS });\n    93→\n    94→      // (c) Pause all SVG SMIL animations\n    95→      await page.evaluate(() => {\n    96→        document.querySelectorAll(\"svg\").forEach((svg) => {\n    97→          if (typeof svg.pauseAnimations === \"function\") {\n    98→            svg.pauseAnimations();\n    99→          }\n   100→        });\n   101→      });\n   102→\n   103→      // (d) Wait for all fonts to finish loading\n   104→      await page.evaluate(() => document.fonts.ready);\n   105→\n   106→      // Settle time for remaining paints\n   107→      await page.waitForTimeout(300);\n   108→\n   109→      return response;\n   110→    };\n   111→\n   112→    await use(page);\n   113→\n   114→    // (e) Assert no console errors after test completes\n   115→    if (consoleErrors.length > 0) {\n   116→      throw new Error(\n   117→        `Console errors detected during test:\\n${consoleErrors.map((e) => `  - ${e}`).join(\"\\n\")}`\n   118→      );\n   119→    }\n   120→  },\n   121→});\n   122→\n   123→export { expect };\n   124→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"37a15401-e0d4-457f-a50f-8f5b7da3be77","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:54:40.286Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts","content":"import { test as base, expect, type Page, type ConsoleMessage } from \"@playwright/test\";\n\nconst FREEZE_CSS = `\n  *, *::before, *::after {\n    animation-duration: 0s !important;\n    animation-delay: 0s !important;\n    transition-duration: 0s !important;\n    transition-delay: 0s !important;\n    scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n  }\n  /* Pause SVG SMIL animations */\n  svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n`;\n\n/**\n * Shared visual-regression fixture.\n *\n * Extends the default Playwright `test` with a `stablePage` fixture that:\n *  (a) Seeds Math.random() and Date.now() for determinism\n *  (b) Injects CSS to disable all CSS + SVG animations/transitions\n *  (c) Pauses SVG SMIL animations via JS\n *  (d) Waits for document.fonts.ready and network idle\n *  (e) Collects console errors and fails the test if any are found\n */\nexport const test = base.extend<{ stablePage: Page }>({\n  stablePage: async ({ page }, use) => {\n    // (e) Collect console errors throughout the test (filtering expected noise)\n    const NOISE_PATTERNS = [\n      \"401\",                 // JWT auth attempts in mock mode (no backend)\n      \"403\",                 // Auth rejection in mock mode\n      \"429\",                 // Rate limit (multiple visual tests hit same endpoints)\n      \"favicon\",             // Missing favicon\n      \"ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED\", // Backend not running in visual test mode\n      \"Failed to fetch\",     // Network requests to non-existent backend\n      \"Failed to load resource\", // Generic resource loading failures (auth, rate limit)\n      \"NetworkError\",        // Same\n    ];\n    const consoleErrors: string[] = [];\n    page.on(\"console\", (msg: ConsoleMessage) => {\n      if (msg.type() === \"error\") {\n        const text = msg.text();\n        if (!NOISE_PATTERNS.some((p) => text.includes(p))) {\n          consoleErrors.push(text);\n        }\n      }\n    });\n\n    // (a) Deterministic Math.random, crypto.getRandomValues, and frozen Date.now\n    await page.addInitScript(() => {\n      // Mulberry32 seeded PRNG — deterministic sequence from seed 42\n      let seed = 42;\n      function mulberry32(): number {\n        seed |= 0;\n        seed = (seed + 0x6d2b79f5) | 0;\n        let t = Math.imul(seed ^ (seed >>> 15), 1 | seed);\n        t = (t + Math.imul(t ^ (t >>> 7), 61 | t)) ^ t;\n        return ((t ^ (t >>> 14)) >>> 0) / 4294967296;\n      }\n\n      Math.random = mulberry32;\n\n      // Also seed crypto.getRandomValues so Keypair.generate() is deterministic\n      crypto.getRandomValues = <T extends ArrayBufferView | null>(array: T): T => {\n        if (array === null) return array;\n        const view = new Uint8Array(\n          (array as ArrayBufferView).buffer,\n          (array as ArrayBufferView).byteOffset,\n          (array as ArrayBufferView).byteLength,\n        );\n        for (let i = 0; i < view.length; i++) {\n          view[i] = Math.floor(mulberry32() * 256);\n        }\n        return array;\n      };\n\n      // Freeze Date.now to a fixed timestamp (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n      const frozen = 1767225600000;\n      Date.now = () => frozen;\n    });\n\n    // Store the original goto so we can wrap it\n    const originalGoto = page.goto.bind(page);\n\n    // Override goto to always wait for fonts + network idle after navigation\n    page.goto = async (url: string, options?: Parameters<typeof page.goto>[1]) => {\n      const response = await originalGoto(url, {\n        waitUntil: \"networkidle\",\n        ...options,\n      });\n\n      // (b) Inject animation-disabling CSS (navigation clears addStyleTag)\n      await page.addStyleTag({ content: FREEZE_CSS });\n\n      // (c) Pause all SVG SMIL animations\n      await page.evaluate(() => {\n        document.querySelectorAll(\"svg\").forEach((svg) => {\n          if (typeof svg.pauseAnimations === \"function\") {\n            svg.pauseAnimations();\n          }\n        });\n      });\n\n      // (d) Wait for all fonts to finish loading\n      await page.evaluate(() => document.fonts.ready);\n\n      // Settle time for remaining paints\n      await page.waitForTimeout(300);\n\n      return response;\n    };\n\n    await use(page);\n\n    // (e) Assert no console errors after test completes\n    if (consoleErrors.length > 0) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `Console errors detected during test:\\n${consoleErrors.map((e) => `  - ${e}`).join(\"\\n\")}`\n      );\n    }\n  },\n});\n\nexport { expect };\n","numLines":124,"startLine":1,"totalLines":124}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0143FQxNENj8ivPJxvQnvkzZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now! The `stablePage` fixture uses `waitUntil: \"networkidle\"` in its `goto` wrapper. When the page loads at `/referrals`, it might try to make some network requests. The mock routes are set up, but `networkidle` might be waiting for all requests to settle.\n\nBut actually, `page.route()` should intercept the requests BEFORE they go to the network. The routes are set up before `goto`, so they should work.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Maybe the issue is that `page.goto()` navigates to `/referrals`, and the page immediately tries to render. \n\nThe wallet isn't connected yet since we haven't clicked the connect button, so the page displays the connection prompt. Once we click connect, the auth flow should trigger. Let me trace through the setup: I'm clearing localStorage with `addInitScript`, then mocking the auth challenge, auth verify, referral code, stats, and earnings endpoints before navigating to the page.\n\nNow I'm walking through what should happen: the page loads with the wallet disconnected, we click the disconnect button, the mock wallet connects with seeded randomness, SessionContext detects the change and calls `authenticate()`, which requests a challenge from the mocked endpoint, signs the message, verifies it against the other mock, and sets authenticated to true so the content appears. But the test times out waiting for that content to show up, which suggests the route mocks might not be matching the actual backend URLs being called.\n\nLet me verify the URL patterns — the backend is at `http://127.0.0.1:3100` with endpoints at `/auth/challenge` and `/auth/verify`, and my route patterns use `**/auth/challenge` and `**/auth/verify`. According to Playwright's documentation, `**` matches any characters including slashes and colons, so those patterns should work. But I should check if there's something else filtering out console errors that might be hiding what's actually happening.\n\nActually, I'm wondering if the issue is with how `networkidle` works in the `goto` wrapper — when the mocked routes respond instantly, the page might still be waiting for the network to settle. Let me try a different approach instead: maybe I can check if the app has a way to skip authentication for visual tests, or just focus on testing the unauthenticated state since that's what the ReferralPage shows when the user isn't logged in.\n\nThe simplest solution is to pre-populate localStorage with session tokens so that when the wallet connects, the SessionProvider immediately finds the existing tokens and sets `isAuthenticated = true` without making any API calls. Looking at how the SessionProvider initializes, it checks for a persisted session and access token, then sets authenticated state if they exist. So I need to figure out what those storage functions do and how to set them up properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2544,"cache_read_input_tokens":104117,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2544},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"579ec3bc-9777-4390-97ad-661f846a5bcf"}
