{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VQzbZoPHZsgRFLdMrJjrph","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still flaky. The routes ARE being matched sometimes (test passes ~50% of the time), but not always. Let me investigate deeper.\n\nThe intermittent nature suggests a race condition. Let me check if there's something about how `goto` with `networkidle` interacts with the route mocking.\n\nWait, I just realized something. The `stablePage.goto` wrapper uses `waitUntil: \"networkidle\"`. When navigating to `/referrals`, the Vite dev server starts loading the JavaScript bundles. Meanwhile, the page might try to make API calls. With `networkidle`, the goto waits until there's no network activity for 500ms.\n\n\nThe problem is that `networkidle` might resolve before the page fully settles—maybe the JS loads and there's a brief quiet period before the page even tries to connect the wallet. Then when we click the connect button, something's still initializing. The timing varies each run, which explains the flakiness.\n\nLet me try a different approach entirely. Instead of relying on route mocking and the unpredictable timing of `networkidle`, I'll set up a pre-existing session in localStorage and use `addInitScript` to inject a mock token directly into the page before any of its JavaScript runs.\n\nOverriding fetch globally...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":524,"cache_read_input_tokens":116304,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":524},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04a5000a-cdc8-4275-a60d-f3cd96e399cf","uuid":"cb88accb-951e-43d4-94fd-f3d2e56329d9"}
